  "texts": [
    "An LSTM is an extension of a recurrent neural network that has feedback connections.",
    "Although other types of RNNs, like RNN, work point by point in the datasets, LSTM works end to end and hence can easily handle and solve time-series data algorithms and classification.",
    "ConvLSTM is an advanced version of LSTM that includes convolutional operations inside the LSTM cell.",
    "It represents a particular kind of RNN that proves to be efficacious for modeling long-term dependencies in a specific manner.",
    "Unlike the standard LSTM structures, in ConvLSTM, matrix operations in each of the gates of the cell are replaced with convolution operations."
  ],
